                    <div class="col">
                        <p>The Mundan ceremony is performed due to a belief that the newborn baby’s hair has the undesired
                             traits of the past life. Hence, the hair of the newborn baby is considered impure as it may have
                              the negative effects of the past life on the future life. So, head shaving is done to purify the
                               soul of the baby and ensure the prosperous life of the baby. It is also believed that Mundan reduces the 
                               body temperature of the baby and making the baby calm. It also enhances and improves the blood circulation. 
                               As per the Vedas, Mundan is a purifying ritual. There are sixteen Sanskars or ceremonies needed to be
                                performed in a person’s life and Mundan puja is one of them. Mundan puja is also known as Chudakarana ceremony
                                 where baby’s hair is shaved off for the first time. Mundan Puja is performed for both boys and girls. 

 
                        </p>
                               
